      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey, i'm looking at a batch of high-end egyptian cotton linen. the spec calls for a super-fine weave, but i'm seeing some inconsistencies in the thread density across the middle of the bolt. what's the best way to scientifically verify if the weave is tight enough to meet the structural integrity requirements for a premium grade? thanks.",
