    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. i tried the thread counter but the density variations are subtle. i'm worried that even if the TPI is technically within range, the gaps in the weave might make it too porous. if the weave isn't sufficiently tight or \"closed,\" what kind of material failures or external penetrations should i be looking for in a high-end linen?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "If the weave is insufficiently closed, you should examine the fabric for micro-puckering or irregular surface texture that suggests gaps between interlacing threads. Functionally, this porosity could lead to premature dye leaching, inconsistent hand-feel, or increased susceptibility to abrasion damage over time. For premium linen, look closely under magnification for pinholes, despite the TPI being nominally correct, as these indicate localized structural weaknesses.",
      "source": "target",
