    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. i'll check for those pinholes. one more thing though—some of the old-school manufacturers i've talked to mention that a super-tight, dense weave is almost like a protective barrier for the fabric itself. from a material science perspective, why is a high density so critical for preventing anything from getting through the fibers?",
